Date: 7/8/1878
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: Yesterday morning on opening the Lands Court, after two days' adjournment to give the natives time to send in their names for certificates for the Kaingaroa Block lately passed through the Court, and awarded to several hapus, the Tapuaka and Ngatipakio hapus, headed by Te Pokiha, and all armed with spears and other weapons, took possession of the Court House.
