Date: 12/2/1777
Source: Log
Author: EDGAR
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: Their Weapons consists of Spears darts and battle Axes & Patoo Patoos - the Patoo Patoo's is an instrument made of bone of large Fish or Stone -it is in shape of a battledore [cf WADDY 1]& about 16 or 18 Inches long,
Notes: 1777 Feb 12 Edgar's Log in 1908 McNab Historical Records 2/225

Date: 0/0/1777
Source: Voyage Round the World
Author: FORSTER
Vol / Page: 1/137
Edition:
Quote: ... we heard a loud hallooing on ... an island, which on this occasion obtained the name of Indian Island; and standing on the shore we perceived one of the natives ... He stood with a club or battle-axe in his hand, ... and behind him ... two women, each of them having a long spear. ... held a long speech ... swing round his club, on which he leaned at other times.
Notes:

Date: 29/11/1791
Source: Journal of Voyage in HMS 'Chatham'
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: But both their Spears and Clubs were subject to great variety. Some of the Spears were very long and pointed only at one end, without much neatness. Their Clubs were rough pieces of Wood, ... and a very few had two stones lashed on at one end, which gave them the appearance of a double-headed maul.
Notes:  [a Moriori spear] 1791 Nov 29 Journal of the Chathamin 1908 McNab Historical Records 2/506

