Edition:
Quote: Tommy said it was next to impossible to attack a New Zealander with a sword ... as they have a method of pushing such weapons aside ... and generally kill the person with a Maree or axe or spear before he has time to make a second thrust.
Notes: 1826 Mar 24 Shepherd Journal in 1940 Howard Rakiura 364

Date: 0/0/1833
Source: Letter
Author: SHERIDAN
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: ... in former days when in battle ... [they had] only their own implements of destruction - spears, nipes, and an instrument made out of beautiful blue or green marble stone, which they call a Mary, none but a chief is allowed to take them to battle, they are very scarce and very dear.
Notes: 1833 Sheridan Letter from <i>Sydney Monitor</i> in 1913 McNab Old Whaling Days 48

